# Whitelist gitignore: ignore everything by default, then explicitly allow site files.
# If a new file doesn't show up in `git status`, it's being ignored on purpose.
# To track something new, add a `!` rule below. Subdirectories need their own `!folder/` rule.

# Ignore everything
*

# Always track this file
!.gitignore

# Site source files
!*.html
!*.css

# Images
!*.webp
!*.jpg
!*.jpeg
!*.png
!*.svg
!*.ico

# Site config and SEO
!robots.txt
!sitemap.xml

# Fonts (if Anna ever self-hosts)
!*.woff
!*.woff2
!*.ttf

# README, if you add one
!README.md
